sentences.english: However, it is rare for an architecture to be totally driven from the top down.
sentences.chinese: 然而，很少有體系架構是完完全全的自頂向下的。

sentences.english: Experience the city's grungier side by exploring this region which is refreshingly down to earth.
sentences.chinese: 通過探尋此地完完全全的真實面來體驗城市的骯髒面。

sentences.english: I tell you now, I made a complete fool of myself.
sentences.chinese: 我現在告訴你，我完完全全的欺騙了我自己。

sentences.english: She has not veered wholly off-course—yet.
sentences.chinese: 到此爲止，她還沒有完完全全偏離自己的軌道。

sentences.english: At this point, I can literally sense the frustration in the room.
sentences.chinese: 在這一刻，我能完完全全地感受到房間裏的挫敗感。

sentences.english: I just wanted to be a ghost, completely anonymous.
sentences.chinese: 我只想像一個孤魂一樣，完完全全地隱姓埋名。

sentences.english: But no one is completely incapable of having fun.
sentences.chinese: 但是沒有誰是完完全全不能娛樂的。

sentences.english: Completely broken my dream that my dream for climbing with see the beautiful sea.
sentences.chinese: 完完全全打破了我想要在青島爬牆看海的美夢。

sentences.english: There seems no be-all-end-all cure for his misbehavior.
sentences.chinese: 對他的不良行爲，似乎沒有完完全全的根治方法。

sentences.english: The smooth gray-brown smoke hangs over the Russian landscape, completely obscuring the ground in places.
sentences.chinese: 滾滾的濃煙盤旋在空中，將俄羅斯完完全全的遮住。

sentences.english: They were kept in complete isolation in this compound.
sentences.chinese: 他們被完完全全隔離在這個隱形後院裏。

definition: lit. from head to tail (idiom); thoroughgoing/through and through/out and out/from top to bottom
one thread, one hair (idiom); a tiny bit/an iota
not in the least/to completely lack
from start to finish/from head to tail/the whole (thing)
